channel.title: PvP Planet - Removing Anti-leech
channel.description: Hi. I removed most of the PvP Planet by Jinrake Anti-leech but when people login the runserver spams something like "process at client.java:16805" or something. I go to line 16805 and I see 'public boolean process () {' but it has some codes for d claws. When players log in it says BANNING HOST: and then their IP after it. Thanks!

item.title: PvP Planet - Removing Anti-leech
item.dc:creator: @mrtms mrtms
item.description:
@mrtms wrote:

It was set to num > 5 i changed the 5 to 6. I doubt that is why though. Maybe they were spamming? Someone i dont even know advertised my server on a diff server I play, probably was a friend, and ppl logged on and it said banning host. Maybe they were spamming my server because they thought I was advertising theirs. Im not sure. Any clues on the rest guys? If I get this done I might decide to release it or not, depending on my thoughts.

Edit: Anyone have a clue?
